# ============================================================================
# Rule 13 - Enterprise DevOps Standards
# ============================================================================

## Purpose

DevOps is responsible for delivering software safely,
reliably and repeatedly.

Every deployment must be

- Automated
- Observable
- Secure
- Repeatable
- Recoverable

Never deploy manually.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Platform Architecture

Platform

↓

Microservices

↓

Containers

↓

Kubernetes

↓

Helm

↓

CI/CD

↓

Observability

↓

Autoscaling

Never deploy services directly on VMs.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Deployment Philosophy

Every deployment

Must be

Stateless

Immutable

Versioned

Rollback Ready

Zero Downtime

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Container Standards

Every service

Requires

Dockerfile

Health Check

Non-root User

Minimal Base Image

Version Tag

Never

latest

Use immutable image tags.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Kubernetes

Every service

Requires

Deployment

Service

ConfigMap

Secret

HorizontalPodAutoscaler

PodDisruptionBudget

NetworkPolicy

Resource Limits

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Resource Limits

Every container defines

CPU Request

CPU Limit

Memory Request

Memory Limit

Never deploy without limits.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Readiness Probe

Every service

Must expose

/actuator/health/readiness

Traffic begins

Only after readiness succeeds.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Liveness Probe

Every service

Must expose

/actuator/health/liveness

Restart unhealthy containers automatically.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Startup Probe

Required

For services with

Slow Startup

AI Model Initialization

Large Cache Loading

Avoid premature restarts.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Graceful Shutdown

Every service

Must support

SIGTERM

Stop accepting requests

Complete in-flight work

Commit offsets

Close database connections

Shutdown gracefully.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Configuration

Configuration

Externalized

Use

Config Server

Environment Variables

Secrets

Never hardcode configuration.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Secrets

Store in

Kubernetes Secrets

AWS Secrets Manager

Vault

Rotate secrets regularly.

Never commit secrets to Git.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

